top.value: This Indefinite Delivery, Indefinite Quantity (IDIQ) Contract for Energy Sector Technical Assistance (TA), Feasibility Studies (FS), and Sector Planning Missions (SPMs) will improve the efficiency and efficacy of USTDA's project planning assistance by developing a pool of highly qualified technical experts to undertake energy-specific TAs, FSs, and SPMs.

The Global Procurement Initiative: Procurement Assistance Program for Thailand is a national-level Program aimed to train Thai procurement officials on international best practices in procurement to obtain the greatest value for money for public investments. The Procurement Assistance Program is made up of four components: (1) A Virtual Training Series composed of up to 10 webinars; (2) a three day In-Country Workshop in Bangkok; (3) a 12-13-calendar day Study Tour to the United States for public procurement leaders; and (4) a Virtual Forum to bring together all participants from the respective training activities for a discussion on change management. The goal of the Program is to build upon technical skills required to be able to procure infrastructure utilizing value-based procurement mechanisms and life-cycle cost analysis.

The Light Aircraft and Helicopter Reverse Trade Mission (RTM) introduced delegates from sub-Saharan Africa to U.S. technology and industry best practices in the aviation sector. Delegates from private sector aviation companies in sub-Saharan Africa participated in site visits where they met with U.S. industry experts and suppliers of light aircraft and helicopters.

The JPS New Kingston Smart City Technical Assistance supports Jamaica Public Service Company Limited in determining the technical, financial, and economic viability of a proposed smart city project for Jamaica. The technical assistance would define up to four smart cities technologies or services for deployment in the demonstration program in New Kingston, and potentially across Jamaica.

A USTDA training grant is supporting the U.S. company Cisco Systems, Inc.'s bid to provide equipment and services for the Philippines's largest telecommunications company, PLDT Inc., to modernize its fiber optic network and transmission infrastructure in the Philippines.

A USTDA grant to Green Liquified Natural Gas Limited is funding a feasibility study that would assess the viability of a 144 tons per day liquefied natural gas liquefaction and distribution facility and associated regasification and distribution stations in Southwestern Nigeria.
